{
  "name": "RPlog_A_Little_Respect",
  "title": "A Little Respect",
  "summary": "Smarting from a failed meeting with Talon Karrde aboard their host's ship, the dark Force-user Simon seeks out the Jedi Jessalyn Valios and, on the advice of their benefactor Orson and his associate Drew, offers to take her clothes-shopping as a gesture of respect. The pair leave the asteroid base and wander the Sunken Esplanade on Asteroid Kappa, where Simon insists on buying her something, eventually settling on practical spacer's wear after an elegant gown proves too costly. As they walk arm in arm, their conversation deepens into a gentle but serious philosophical debate: Simon, raised in the Selas tradition that the soul is precious and fragile, confesses he sinned against her by touching her mind, while Jessalyn, as Luke Skywalker's student, argues that healing another's soul consensually can be an act of intimacy and compassion, not corruption. Neither fully convinces the other, but the exchange draws them closer, each quietly hoping to lead the other toward their own path, before they agree it is getting late and turn back toward the ship.",
